 utilizing a\nmultiple object spectrograph with a large field of view; e.g. the Prime Focus\nSpectrograph mounted on Subaru Telescope. The above estimation has several\nadvantages: The data-driven estimation of the contamination makes the analysis\nof the astrophysical factor stable against the complicated foreground\ndistribution. Besides, foreground contamination effect is considered in the\nlikelihood analysis.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 17 Jun 2017 06:04:54 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 29 Aug 2018 20:02:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-08-31"}
